# Airtable Button — Usage Rules

When generating or editing code that uses `Button` from `@airtable/blocks/ui`:

## Variants

- `default` — generic actions, toolbar buttons. Background: `#F2F2F2`, text: `#333333`.
- `primary` — the single most important action on a screen or modal. Background: `#2D7FF9`, text: white. **NEVER more than one per surface.**
- `secondary` — cancel/back controls. Background: transparent (NOT gray). Pairs with `primary` in confirm/cancel patterns.
- `danger` — irreversible destructive actions only (delete, revoke, remove). Background: `#EF3061`, text: white. **NEVER use for cancel, back, or close.**

## Props

- No `loading` prop exists. Disable the button and update the label text instead (`{isSaving ? 'Saving…' : 'Save'}`).
- `icon` is always left-aligned. There is no `rightIcon` or `iconRight` prop.
- Icon-only buttons (no `children`) **MUST** have `aria-label`. Omitting it throws a runtime console error.
- Use `type="submit"` on buttons inside `<form>` elements.

## Sizes

- `small` — dense toolbars, table row actions
- `default` — most contexts
- `large` — primary CTAs in onboarding or marketing flows

Responsive size is supported: `size={{ xsmallViewport: 'small', mediumViewport: 'default' }}`

## Tokens (use these, not raw hex)

| Token | Value | Used for |
|---|---|---|
| `Light gray 2` | `#F2F2F2` | default button background |
| `blueBright` | `#2D7FF9` | primary button background |
| `red` | `#EF3061` | danger button background — NOT `#F82B60` |
| `Dark` | `#333333` | default + secondary button text |
| `White` | `#FFFFFF` | primary + danger button text |

## What doesn't exist

- No `loading` prop
- No `rightIcon` or `iconRight` prop
- No `xlarge` size (only on TextButton, not Button)
- `secondary` has no background fill — it is intentionally transparent

## Do not confuse with TextButton

`TextButton` is a different component that renders as `<span>`. Use `Button` for all interactive actions that require keyboard accessibility and a native button element.
